 } } \right|$$ 
<br><br>Applying c<sub>1</sub> $$ \to $$ c<sub>1</sub> + c<sub>2</sub> + c<sub>3</sub>
<br><br>$$ = \,\,\,\,\left| {\matrix{
   {5x - 4} &amp; {2x} &amp; {2x}  \cr 
   {5x - 4} &amp; {x - 4} &amp; {2x}  \cr 
   {5x - 4} &amp; {2x} &amp; {x - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$
<br><br>Taking common (5x $$-$$ 4) from c<sub>1</sub> 
<br><br>$$ = \,\,\,\,\left( {5x - 4} \right)\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; {2x} &amp; {2x}  \cr 
   1 &amp; {x - 4} &amp; {2x}  \cr 
   1 &amp; {2x} &amp; {x - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$
<br><br>Apply R<sub>2</sub> $$ \to $$R<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ R<sub>1</sub>  and R<sub>3</sub> $$ \to $$R<sub>3</sub> $$-$$ R<sub>1</sub>
<br><br>$$ = \,\,\,\,\left( {5x - 4} \right)\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; {2x} &amp; {2x}  \cr 
   0 &amp; { - \left( {x + 4} \right)} &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; { - \left( {x + 4} \right)}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$ 
<br><br>$$ = \,\,\,\,\left( {5x - 4} \right){\left( {x + 4} \right)^2}$$
<br><br>So, (A + Bx) (x $$-$$ A)<sup>2</sup>  = (5x $$-$$ 4) (x + 4)<sup>2</sup> 
<br><br>By comparing both sides we get,  A = $$-$$ 4  and B  =  5
